latestPosts.caption:
Woke up in our cozy @airbnb , and knew I had to start the day with a little act of service.
.
As soon as we landed in Phuket and walked into a 7-Eleven, I picked up a few essentials to whip up breakfast for Muskaan. I’ve always been good with oats - so I fancied them up with banana and strawberries. Grabbed cheese sandwiches too. And of course, instant noodles! A bit tricky to figure out, but with some help from a translator app, I nailed it.

For drinks, I made myself a protein shake and served Muskaan some leftover mango shake from the night before - homemade with fresh mangoes and milk.

This is exactly why we love staying at Airbnbs. Slow mornings, cozy kitchens, and the comfort of living like locals - not guests.

Thank you, @airbnb, for picking up the tab.

Our favorite experience from Thailand. Details below ❤️🌴⬇️
.
👉🏻Location: Phi Phi Islands, Thailand📍
👉🏻Activity: Beat-the-Crowd Sunrise Tour of Phi Phi Islands 
👉🏻We reached every spot early and had them almost all to ourselves✨
👉🏻Places covered: Maya Bay, Pileh Lagoon, Viking Cave, Ko Rang Yai Beach😍
👉🏻The tour began at sunrise (5 AM) and ended by 2 PM
👉🏻Inclusions: Breakfast, lunch, snacks, soft drinks, water, and fruits - everything was taken care of! It was a fully guided, all-inclusive experience with pickup and drop-off from our stay in Phuket
👉🏻Cost: ₹10K–12K per person
👉🏻We booked it via @headout and it was worth every penny. If you’re visiting Thailand, we highly recommend doing this Phi Phi sunrise tour with Headout!
.
